# Philadelphia Rolls

Based on [https://pickledplum.com/philadelphia-roll/](https://pickledplum.com/philadelphia-roll/) ([wayback](http://web.archive.org/web/20250801063948/https://pickledplum.com/philadelphia-roll/))

{ rating="0" image="None" }
:::
:::

## Ingredients

- [ ] Smoked salmon (cold-smoked preferred)
- [ ] Cream cheese, softened
- [ ] Cucumber
- [ ] Sushi rice
- [ ] Nori
- [ ] Sesame seeds (optional)

## Recipe

1. Cut nori sheet in half. Spread rice over the nori, then sprinkle with sesame seeds if using
1. Flip the nori so rice side is down
1. Spread a thin layer of cream cheese over the nori
1. Add strips of cucumber and smoked salmon
1. Roll tightly and slice into 6-8 pieces

## Notes

1. The cream cheese balances the intense smokiness of the salmon, making this a perfect fusion roll
1. Cold-smoked salmon has better texture for sushi than hot-smoked
1. Use thin slices of smoked salmon to prevent overwhelming the other flavors
1. Can add avocado for extra creaminess
1. This Western-style roll works precisely because it doesn’t try to replicate delicate fresh fish nigiri
